The paper deals with network scanning tools and their role in Internet security, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on ZMap, a tool used for high-speed Internet-wide scanning, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also presents novel identification methods, which involve data analysis and pattern recognition, falling under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to identify and characterize ZMap scans, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
